prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the "Pink Anime Motorcycle Spec Poster Style" visual style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Motorcycle: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these literal style rules. Composition: create a dense premium motorsport dossier on a warm cream page; reserve the upper-left for an enormous italic model-code headline; place a monochrome hot-magenta halftone echo of the rider in the upper-right; show one motorcycle dominating the lower-middle in a low front three-quarter view; place one full-body original cel-shaded rider beside and partly overlapping the machine; finish the lower area with three bordered close-up panels and a compact black technical specification card. For 4:5, use a tall stacked reading path; for 5:4, widen the same hierarchy into a compact landscape editorial spread. Typography: use extra-bold italic condensed sans for the main code, compact uppercase technical grotesk for annotations, slanted magenta label ribbons, vertical side text, thin rules, and one short brush-italic closing phrase. Color: keep roughly sixty-five percent warm cream, twenty percent hot pink or magenta, ten percent black and white, and five percent motorcycle-specific accent color. Texture and lighting: pair polished semi-real motorcycle materials with clean anime cel shading, subtle paper grain, fine halftone dots, crisp edges, bright soft studio light, controlled paint reflections, and a low soft contact shadow. Graphic elements: use checkered micro-strips, triple slashes, racing-number boxes, small arrows, speed sparkles, diagonal bands, three inspection crops, and a black angled specification block. Make the four-case system feel like one collectible series. Keep all text original, short, and graphic. Render a finished premium poster, not a sketch.

Avoid: copied source character, copied face or pose, the source race car, copied pink livery, copied title or slogans, exact layout tracing, copied brand or sponsor logos, manufacturer badges, creator signature, watermark, username, QR code, platform mark, multiple motorcycles, photoreal person, live-action photography, dark street scene, cinematic background, cyberpunk neon, sparse minimalist layout, rough storyboard, malformed wheels, extra limbs, or unreadable paragraph text.

Important content rule: match the reference style system first, then change the source content. Every sample must feature one new motorcycle and one new original rider while preserving the same typography, cream-magenta palette behavior, halftone echo, technical panel strip, and dense editorial hierarchy.
